{
    "word": "Neuroglia",
    "definitions": [
        "The delicate connective tissue framework which supports the nervous matter and blood vessels of the brain and spinal cord; called also K. It is composed of cells which are not neurons. Once thought to serve merely a supporting funciton, they are now believed to have important metablolic functions. Among them are the astrocytes, ependymal cells, oligodendroglia cells, and microglia cells."
    ],
    "examples": [
    ],
    "etymology": "[NL., fr. Gr. ney^ron ligament + gli`a glue.]"
}